<HEADLINE> Heroic Welcome Greets Hamas Leader's Return to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of cheering
Palestinians in Gaza today granted a heroic welcome to Sheikh
Ahmed Yassin, the founder and spiritual leader of the radical
Islamic group Hamas.
</P>
<P>
Yassin was flown from Jordanian capital Amman this afternoon
in a Jordanian military helicopter to a tumultuous welcome by
cheering Palestinian residents and Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) officials.
</P>
<P>
Posters and freshly painted slogan in the walls of buildings
congratulated the return of Yassin, who has been imprisoned by
Israel for nine years and was released last week in a prisoner
exchange deal reached between Israel and Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Yassin's release was reportedly part of a deal to release the
two alleged special agents from Israeli secret service Mossad,
who were detained for trying to assassinate Hamas leader in
Jordan Khaled Mashal.
</P>
<P>
Shortly before Yassin's arrival in Gaza, the two agents
returned to Israel. And 20 prisoners, 11 Palestinians and nine
Jordanians, were released from Israeli prisons apparently as
part of the exchange deal.
</P>
<P>
Media reports said Jordanian King Hussein spoke with Israeli
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu by phone today over the
return of Yassin, but the Prime Minister's Office here denied
the reports.
</P>
<P>
Yassin, who held a chaotic news conference before leaving
Amman, vowed to carry on Hamas' fight against Israel occupation
despite his claim that Hamas activists were peace-seekers.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Israel must recognize the rights of the
Palestinians' return to their homeland and release all
Palestinian prisoners, otherwise there could be no cease-fire to
end Hamas' violent attacks against Israeli targets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
