<HEADLINE> Hamed to Face Badillo to Defend WBO Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Naseem Hamed will meet challenger
Jose Badillo of Puerto Rico to defend his WBO featherweight title
on Saturday night at Sheffield Arena.
</P>
<P>
Badillo, the WBO's No. 1 contender, replaces Colombia's Victor
Llerena, who agreed to step aside after being compensated, as the
challenger for Hamed's crown.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Badillo has a record of 20 wins and one
defeat. Fight promoter Frank Warren said Badillo was a better
opponent than Llerena.
</P>
<P>
Hamed-Badillo is one of three world title fights scheduled for
Saturday in Sheffield.
</P>
<P>
Chris Eubank will face Jose Calzaghe for the vacant WBO
super-middleweight title, and Ryan Rhodes was due to fight
Canada's Otis Grant for the vacant WBO middleweight crown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
