<HEADLINE> First Pan-African Education TV Channel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The first pan-African
distance learning television channel is to start broadcasting
soon from Namibia to viewers of five English-speaking African
countries.
</P>
<P>
The station is known as Global Education Network Africa or
GENA, the Southern African Broadcasting Association (SABA)
reported from Windhoek, capital of Namibia today.
</P>
<P>
It will broadcasting five days a week to Kenya, Namibia,
Swaziland, Tanzania and Uganda.
</P>
<P>
GENA is to broadcast a mix of adult educational programs,
distance learning courses and support programs for secondary
education, Radio Namibia was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The program will enable people with access to television to
upgrade and refine their skills and knowledge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
