<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Chi Haotian, vice-chairman of
the Central Military Commission, met with Augusto Pinochet Ugarte,
commander-in-chief of the Chilean Army, here today.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who also serves as a state councillor and defense
minister, said the Sino-Chilean relationship, including military
relationships, have developed smoothly despite the geographical
separation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
China and Chile are influential countries, said Chi, noting
that the steady development of friendship and cooperation between
the two sides has contributed to peace and stability in the
Asia-Pacific region and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Chi said Pinochet's visit will advance the development of the
friendship and cooperation between the two countries and between
their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet offered his congratulations on the success of the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China and on China's
achievements in economic construction.
</P>
<P>
He expressed delight on visiting China again, and noted that
communications between the two armies will be very helpful in
strengthening the relations between the two countries and between
their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Qian Shugen, deputy chief of the General Staff of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army, met with Pinochet Monday and attended
today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean delegation arrived in China Monday as guests of the
Headquarters of the PLA General Staff. 
</P>
