<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, US to Promote Bilateral Economic and Trade Ties (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States will
take the forthcoming Chinese President Jiang Zemin's state visit
to the US as an opportunity to expand their economic and trade
relations.
</P>
<P>
Wu Yi, Chinese minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC), and the visiting US Commerce Secretary
William Daley expressed this common belief at the 11th Session of
the Sino-US Joint Committee on Commerce and Trade (JCCT), which
opened here today and was co-chaired by the two ministers.
</P>
<P>
The annual meeting was held on the eve of Jiang's state visit
to the US and this "is of special significance," Wu Yi said,
hoping that the two countries would plan their economic and trade
relations strategically, and will further develop such relations.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-US relations are at an important moment, Daley said,
adding that President Jiang Zemin will soon visit the US and
President Bill Clinton will visit China next year and the two
nations should use the opportunity to push forward the bilateral
economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that MOFTEC has established and developed good
relations of cooperation with the US Department of Commerce in
recent years through the JCCT.
</P>
<P>
Wu added that Sino-US economic and trade relations have
developed healthily in an all-round way.
</P>
<P>
She said Daley's visit will "inject new impetus into bilateral
economic and trade relations."
</P>
<P>
Wu also noted that new progress has been made in Sino-US economic
and trade ties since the 10th session of the JCCT, which was held in
Washington last year.
</P>
<P>
Issues of intellectual property rights and textiles have been
resolved, bilateral trade and two-way investments have increased
steadily, exchanges of commodities are becoming more active, US
industrial and commerce enterprises are becoming more and more
involved in China's constructions, and the negotiations between
the two nations on China's entry into the World Trade Organization
(WTO) have shown a positive momentum, Wu recalled.
</P>
<P>
She said that the JCCT meetings in the last couple of years
have laid a solid foundation for an effective cooperation between
two sides in the economic and trade fields, and the very purpose
of the current meeting is to push such cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Daley said that the JCCT has already become a good mechanism
for maintaining contacts and dialogues between the two countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971007.0027 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, US to Promote Bilateral Economic and Trade Ties (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the MFN issue, Wu said the US side "can do something" so as
to thoroughly resolve this issue at an early date, which has long
been troubling Sino-US economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Talking about China's entering the World Trade Organization
(WTO), Wu reiterated that China's request to enter the
organization demonstrates the country's determination and
confidence in opening up wider to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
As a major signatory state of the WTO, Wu said, the US should
take a reasonable attitude and honor its promises, and play a
positive role.
</P>
<P>
Daley said the US side regards US-China ties as very important
and wants to see China entering the WTO, because this not only is
in the interests of China but also of the US.
</P>
<P>
Touching on the US "sanctions" on China, the Chinese minister
pointed out that the US removal of some of its so-called
"sanctions" against China, which obstruct bilateral cooperation
and contacts, will enjoy popular confidence at a time when the
Sino-US economic and trade ties are developing fast.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the loans of the Export-Import Bank of the US and
financial issues, Wu noted the US financial institutions have
offered strong support to American exporters, increasing the
competitiveness of their products.
</P>
<P>
She added that this is an important way to balance the trade
deficit of the US with China.
</P>
<P>
Coming back to the issue of textile products, Wu said she hopes
the US side would present specific cases of illegal transhipment
for the two sides to clarify the responsibilities, work together
to fight against such activities and to eventually remove this
obstacle in textile trade.
</P>
<P>
On the cooperation in space technology, Wu said he hopes the US
government would simplify and accelerate the formalities in
approving China's launching of US-made satellites.
</P>
<P>
She also hoped the issue of export control on meteorological
satellites can be resolved early so as to promote the further
cooperation between space industries of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that in dealing with economic and trade
ties, it is important to maintain contacts and dialogues, which
will help increase mutual understanding, reduce differences and
enhance cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
