<HEADLINE> Iran Not Hurry for Return of European Ambassadors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Iranian foreign minister said
here today that there is no hurry on the part of Iran for return
of the European ambassadors to Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Kamal Kharrazi made the remark while delivering a report on his
mission in the United Nations General Assembly at today's
Parliament session.
</P>
<P>
"It's up to the European ambassadors to take decision in this
respect. What is of importance to us is the strength of the
Islamic Republic of Iran," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the return of the European ambassadors, he said, it is a
mutual issue between Iran and Germany and it should be settled by
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Iran has said that ambassadors can return but that the German
envoy must be the last to go back. Germany, backed by its European
Union partners, has rejected the proposal.
</P>
<P>
However, German Foreign Ministry on Sunday rebuffed an Iranian
offer of bilateral talks to solve the dispute blocking the return
of EU ambassadors to Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Germany said that Bonn would only hold talks when the EU
envoys are back in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
EU's 15 members, except Greece, called back their
ambassadors from Tehran after a German court ruled in April
that Iranian leaders ordered the 1992 killing of four dissidents
in Berlin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
