<HEADLINE> Leading Securities Company Reports Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The past five years have
witnessed a rapid growth of the securities underwriting and
brokering business of the China Securities Company Ltd, one of the
three top securities firms in China.
</P>
<P>
The company now has 90 securities branches in more than 20
provinces and municipalities, and the total volume of its
securities trading, in which it either traded on its own or acted
as a broker, has been growing steadily during the period to 460
billion yuan last year, said Shao Chun, president of the China
Securities Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The figure was 8.4 times that of 1995, the second biggest for
all the Chinese securities firms, he added.
</P>
<P>
Shao said his company grew in tandem with the young securities
market. The Chinese stock market as a main part has more than 700
companies listed for the present, with its market capitalization
exceeding 1.62 trillion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, China Securities has acted as the lead
underwriter and listing recommender for the stock placement of
nearly 70 firms, according to Shao.
</P>
<P>
As one of the first batch of approved primary dealers of the
treasury bonds, it has also underwritten a total of 5.65 billion
yuan's worth of government bonds so far.
</P>
<P>
The company also made fruitful attempts in perfecting its
information network, while achieving headway in the investment
bank services and other news services such as the setting up
investment funds and developing financial derivatives. Its
international business is also on steady rise, together with a
gradual formation of a network of overseas clients, Shao added.
</P>
