<HEADLINE> Chi Haotian Meets Indonesian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian said today that strengthening Sino-Indonesian friendship
and cooperation not only is in the fundamental interests of the
two peoples, but is also conducive to safeguarding peace and
stability in the Asia-Pacific Region.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also a State Councillor and vice-chairman of China's
Central Military Commission, made the remarks today in a meeting
with Indonesian Minister of Defense and Security Edi Sudrajat.
</P>
<P>
Chi said that China and Indonesia are two influential and
peace-loving countries in Asia which share identical or similar
views on many important international issues.
</P>
<P>
He said Edi's visit to China will undoubtedly further the
friendship and cooperation between the two countries and their
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Chi also briefed the visitors on the recent 15th National Congress
of the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
Edi said that China plays a vital role in ensuring peace and
stability in Asia, and expressed his pleasure that Sino-Indonesian
relations have witnessed continuous development.
</P>
<P>
He noted that both Indonesia and China have great potential
for development and will make even greater contributions to world
peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Edi expressed the hope for expanded friendly exchanges between
the armed forces of the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the meeting, Chi held a ceremony to welcome the
Indonesian visitors who arrived here this morning as guests of the
Chinese defense minister.  
</P>
</TEXT>
