<HEADLINE> Indonesian President to Attend AELM in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
will attend the 5th Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC)
Economic Leaders Meeting (AELM) to be held in Vancouver, Canada,
on November 24, a senior official said here today.
</P>
<P>
"President Soeharto has decided to go to Vancouver,"
Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono said after accompanying the
president to receive visiting Canadian Ambassador for APEC Affairs
Leonard Edward at the Merdeka Palace.
</P>
<P>
Moerdiono said the president has decided to attend the AELM
because the meeting is not only important to Indonesia and Canada
but also to countries in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
"The APEC is important to Asia-Pacific countries in entering
the 21st century," the president was quoted as saying by
Moerdiono.
</P>
<P>
He also said all APEC members have agreed to implement APEC
trade liberalization gradually, with developed countries scheduled
to implement it by 2010 at the latest and developing countries by
2020 at the latest.
</P>
<P>
Formed in 1989, the APEC forum groups Australia, Brunei,
Canada, China, China's Hong Kong, Chinese Taipei, Indonesia,
Japan, South Korea, New Zealand, Mexico, Chile, the Philippines,
Thailand, Singapore, Malaysia, Papua New Guinea and the United
States.  
</P>
