<DOCNO> XIE19971007.0052 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wang Wins First Diving Gold for Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Unheralded Wang Tianling beat
Olympic silver medalist Yu Zhuocheng to win the gold medal of the
men's one-meter springboard for host Shanghai in the 8th Chinese
National Games here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Wang trailed Yu by 16.16 points before the last dive but he
beat the Atlanta Olympian to second place with a nearly flawless
final dive which earned him 79.2 points.
</P>
<P>
Yu, from China's diving powerhouse Guangdong Province, made a
fatal slip in the board before starting the last dive, which only
got 59.45 points.
</P>
<P>
Wang, 20, cheered on by a fervent home crowd, had led Yu by
15.12 points with a total of 417.30 in semifinals. He accumulated
432.66 points for the win, only 3.64 ahead of Yu.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Yilin from Shanxi Province settled for third with 423.06
points.
</P>
<P>
Yu, who teamed up with Barcelona Olympic platform champion Sun
Shuwei and another star diver Lan Wei to anchor the men's team
title on Sunday, was believed to be a sure shot at the one-meter
board in absence of Olympic champion Xiong Ni.
</P>
<P>
Three time Olympian Xiong finally fulfilled his gold dream in
Atlanta last year after taking a silver in Seoul in 1988 and a
bronze in Barcelona in 1992. The veteran from Hunan Province had
quit the one-meter event to focus on his favorite three-meter
board.
</P>
<P>
The week-long diving competition features eight events,
including men's and women's teams, one-meter and three-meter
springboard and 10-meter platform.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong province swept the team titles while the women's
10-meter platform gold medal went to Wang Rui of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The 8th National Games, China's biggest sports gala before the
turn of the 21st century, will officially open on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
