<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 52.12 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 7 (Xinhua)-- The Sensitive Index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market today gained 52.12 points to
3909.46 as against yesterday's close of 3857.34.
</P>
<P>
The National Index advanced by 18.88 points to 1692.42 from the
previous close of 1673.54.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar indexes were quoted
substantially up at 378.64 and 174.29 compared with yesterday's
closes of 374.51 and 172.39 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Most of share prices on the BSE market today rallied smartly,
pushing the Sensitive Index up by more than 52 points on renewed
buying support from operators as well as fresh purchases by
financial institutions and foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
The BSE Sensitive Index, which showed a narrow movement of
about 30 points till the pre-closing session, suddenly surged to
close near the intra-day high at 3909.46. The revival of support
by foreign institutional investors coupled with purchases by
financial institutions led the bull operators to make fresh
commitments. 
</P>
