<HEADLINE> Chinese, Mozambican Premiers Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng warmly
welcomed Mozambican Prime Minister Pascoal Manuel Mocumbi to China
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li asked Mocumbi to convey President Jiang Zemin's best regards
to Mozambican President Joaquim Alberto Chissano.
</P>
<P>
Li said that friendly and cooperative ties between the two
countries have witnessed continuous development, adding that China
treasures its traditional friendship with Mozambique and is ready
to cooperate with Mozambique to raise the relationship to a new
height.
</P>
<P>
Li addressed bilateral economic and trade relations by
expressing the hope of exploring diverse methods of cooperation
and ensuring more flexible and rewarding cooperative forms.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Premier pointed out that Mozambique is blessed with
good natural conditions and has broad prospects for
development. While noting the country is experiencing some
difficulties in the course of development, Li expressed his firm
belief that the Mozambican government and people will be able to
overcome all obstacles and score new progress in national
construction.
</P>
<P>
Li said that Africa is a continent with full development
potential, and pointed to the solid basis for traditional
friendship between China and African nations.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that China will continue its long-term support for
African nations in efforts to safeguard state sovereignty and
develop their national economies, and will fully support their
reasonable propositions and just demands in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi conveyed President Chissano's best wishes to Chinese
President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Li's visit to Mozambique earlier this year led to
new development in bilateral relations and solved various problems
related to economic cooperation. He also noted broad prospects for
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi said that Mozambique ministers in his delegation have
joined in fruitful discussions with their Chinese counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Railways Minister Han Zhubin also attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Li and his wife hosted a banquet in honor of
Mocumbi and his wife. 
</P>
