<HEADLINE> Beijing Romps into China Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Guo'an on Tuesday
blanked Chinese Army 3-0 in the Beijing Workers' Stadium for an
aggregate 8-0 victory, reaching the final of the Chinese Soccer
Association Cup.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, a front-runner in the Chinese first division league
for the past three years, won the first leg away in a score of 5-0.
</P>
<P>
Russian Andres Olivas Rubio opened the scoring at the 45th
minute as Chinese Army's goalkeeper Li Lei dribbled in his own
penalty box instead of blasting away the ball.
</P>
<P>
Andres found the net again at the 51st minute and Wang Tao
completed the tally 13 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Beijing will vie for the cup with former league winner Shanghai
Shenhua on December 17. 
