<HEADLINE> Economic Climate in Europe Favorable: EU Surveys </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Union countries
have bolstered economic optimism due to strong exports as
demonstrated in rising industrial, consumer and retail trade
confidence.
</P>
<P>
The favorable economic climate was reported today by the
European Commission, the executive body of the 15-nation union,
through business and consumer surveys.
</P>
<P>
The overall sentiment was up by more than 10 percent as
compared with the indicator of 1985.
</P>
<P>
The industrial confidence indicator remained unchanged at a
level above the average over the last decade while consumer and
retail trade confidence also reflected stable gains in confidence.
</P>
<P>
The only decline was found in the construction sector that
dropped slightly, mainly because of erratic movements in the
Spanish figure, according to the surveys. 
</P>
