<DOCNO> XIE19971007.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Annual Inflation Rises to 1.8 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)'s annual
inflation rate rose to 1.8 percent in August from 1.7 percent in
July, Eurostat, the statistical body of the 15-nation union,
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The increase is registered in every EU member state except
Britain, Ireland, Italy and Belgium, the Eurostat report said.
</P>
<P>
French and Finnish rates were both up from 1.1 percent to 1.6
percent; Austria hiked up from 0.9 percent to 1.3 percent; Sweden
gained from 1.8 percent to 2.2 percent; the Netherlands rose from
2.1 percent to 2.5 percent, and Greece increased from 5.2 percent
to 5.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Ireland recorded the lowest rate with a decline from 1.5
percent a month ago to 0.6 percent. The next lowest was Austria.
</P>
<P>
The EU's annual inflation was 2.2 percent a year ago, according
to Eurostat.
</P>
<P>
The figures were calculated as a weighted average of the
harmonized indices of consumer prices (HICPs) in accordance with
the new European index of consumer prices.
</P>
<P>
The HICPs are an important indicator for EU member states which
must meet the criterion on price stability for the European
Economic and Monetary Union (EMU). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971007.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Becker to Be Manager of German Davis Cup Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 7, (Xinhua) -- Boris Becker is to replace Niki
Pilic as manager of Germany's Davis Cup team, the German Tennis
Federation (DTB) said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Pilic, the current captain and manager, was expected to step
down around the end of next year. But he would remain as DTB
consultant for the next two year.
</P>
<P>
The DTB explained that the decision did not indicate any
dissatisfaction with Pilic, who would leave his position ahead of
time. The DTB just did not want to miss the opportunity to get
Becker into the team.
</P>
<P>
Former Davis Cup player Carl-Uwe Steeb, who helped Germany to
their first triumph in 1988, was named team captain.
</P>
<P>
Becker and Steeb will both have a say in team selection but
Becker will have overall managerial responsibility. 
</P>
