<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Development Along Yangtze River Offers Opportunities to Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Leaders from provinces,
municipalities, cities and state-owned corporations along China's
longest Yangtze River here today welcomed investors all over the
world to join the drive to develop the river basin.
</P>
<P>
The further opening up and development of the areas along the
Yangtze River will generate enormous business opportunities for
investors, Tong Qiqing, president of China Changjiang (Yangtze
River) Development Group, told a seminar on Development along the
Yangtze River at the 28th General Assembly of the World Trade
Centers Association (ETCA), which opened here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The group was established on September 28, 1992 in Shanghai's
Pudong. It is designed to band together the upper reaches, middle
reaches and lower reaches of the river for common progress.
</P>
<P>
The group aims to develop commerce and trade, consumer products
manufacturing, transportation and real estate in cities along the
river.
</P>
<P>
Following the successful implementation of the opening policy
along the coastal areas, the Chinese government has decided to
shift its strategic emphasis to the development along the Yangtze
River.
</P>
<P>
The Yangtze River Delta and the Yangtze River region cover a
vast stretch of land, which is abundant in natural resources and
excels in industries and technologies.
</P>
<P>
The 6,380 kilometer-long Yangtze runs through nine provinces
and municipalities: Shanghai, Jiangsu, Zhejiang, Anhui, Jiangxi,
Hubei, Hunan, Sichuan and Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
Besides, a well-developed land transportation network which is
composed of railways, highways and express ways have taken shape
in the areas.
</P>
<P>
The drainage area of the river hits 1.8 million square
kilometers, one fifth of China's land area, which is dwelled by 42
percent of the country's 1.2 billion population.
</P>
<P>
Xu Zhongmin, deputy mayor of Chongqing, the biggest economic
center in the upper reaches, told participants of the seminar that
his city will act in accordance with international practice and
carry on the treatment of Chinese citizens to overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
He promised that Chongqing is duty-bound to protect the legal
rights and interests of the investors so long as they engage in
legal operation.
</P>
<P>
The further opening-up and development of the areas along the
Yangtze River can quickly spread the energies of these areas to
the whole country so as to expedite the economic take-off of the
Chinese mainland, Han Zhongxue, deputy mayor of Wuhan city in
central China's Hubei province, said at the seminar.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan, located in the middle section of the Yangtze River, is
an important link between the eastern, western, northern and
southern parts of China with advanced transportation and
communication systems.
</P>
<P>
The city is also one of the educational and technological bases
of China.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan looks forward to cooperating with countries across the
world in business, finance and industries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, standing at the outlet of the Yangtze River into the
sea, is the largest economic center in China.
</P>
<P>
So far, Shanghai has established trade relations with more than
40,000 businesses in 205 countries and regions around the world
and has more than 10 major export and import markets, said Hua
Yequan, vice-chairman of the WTCA Shanghai branch.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Shanghai absorbed nine billion U.S. dollars in
contracted foreign investment, up 36.23 percent from the previous
year. At present, more than half of the world's top 100 industrial
multinational corporations have invested in Shanghai
</P>
<P>
The rate of success of overseas-invested enterprises in
Shanghai stands as high as 95 percent. Over 80 percent of
overseas-invested enterprises are profitable after they went into
operation.
</P>
<P>
Hua said he believes that based upon equality and mutual
assistance, the economic and trade cooperation between Shanghai
and other places around the world will be more extensive.
</P>
<P>
The super large water conservancy project on earth -- the
Yangtze Three Gorges Project is well under way. By the year 2009
when the project is completed, the river basin area will benefit
in terms of flood control, power generation and navigation.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was chaired by Annie Wu, deputy chairman and
secretary general of the 28 WTCA General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Guy Tozzoli, president of the WTCA, and Chang Wan-Fung,
chairman of Hong Kong Wen Wei Po Daily, co-organizer of the
seminar, delivered opening and closing speeches respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
