<HEADLINE> 23 Die in Kampala Traffic Accidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kampala, October 7 (Xinhua)-- 23 people died and 238 got
injured in traffic accidents last month in Kampala, capital of
Uganda, reported the local press today.
</P>
<P>
The latest police statistics here were quoted as saying though
the death toll is still high, the figure showed a 13 percent
reduction as compared to the month of August.
</P>
<P>
What's more, there was a further reduction of 5 percent in the
number of vehicles involved in accidents as compared to August.
</P>
<P>
In September, the statistics said, there were 459 accidents
with 22 fatal cases and over 637 motor vehicles were involved in
accidents while 48 motor cycles were involved.
</P>
<P>
According to Turyagumanawe, Kampala area traffic officer, the
extra vigilance of traffic police is responsible for the
remarkable reduction in accidents last month.
</P>
<P>
He said driving when drunk has been the major cause of
accidents at night. 
</P>
