<HEADLINE> More Tourists to Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The secretary made these remarks on Monday while addressing an
on-going meeting of Macao's overseas tourism offices in 13
countries and regions. The meeting will close at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
"The increase in visitors' arrival shows that Macao is still a
good sightseeing place," he said. "Confidence has again returned
to heart of visitors."
</P>
<P>
He blamed the drop in the number of visitors over the past few
months on both interior factors (rising crime rates) and
outside ones.
</P>
<P>
Fewer people visited Hong Kong during the handover period,
which resulted in a drop in the number of visitors from Hong Kong,
he said. Hong Kong is the dominant source of visitors for Macao.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the financial crisis in the Southeast Asian
nations has also cut the number of visitors from the regions.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that tourist arrivals dropped 7.7 percent
in the first seven months of the year, and in August alone, the
number plummeted by 36.7 percent, or 314,00 visitors, compared
with the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Tourism officials predicted that visitor arrivals will rise for
the rest of the year, and that the number of visitors for the
whole year will be about the same as last year. 
</P>
