Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, a full-day
China Investment Policy Seminar is scheduled for Wednesday, with
senior officials from China's key ministries updating local
investors on the investment climate and policies in the interior
areas.
</P>
<P>
By the end of August 1997, some 297,000 overseas-funded
enterprises had been approved to operate in China's interior, with
actual investment topping 200 billion U.S. dollars, figures from
the ministry show.
</P>
<P>
Direct overseas investment came from some 160 countries and
regions, with Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan contributing the biggest
slice.
</P>
<P>
Infrastructure projects such as power, road and port projects
have become new attractions to foreign investors. 
