rebels this morning during a transport flight from Trincomalee,
Eastern province, to Elephant Pass, Northern province, but no one
was hurt in the attack.
</P>
<P>
Military spokesman Ink Dewage said today that the choppers were
flying over the sea five kilometers northeast of Mullaitivu,
Northern province, when the rebels in two boats launched the
attack.
</P>
<P>
Pilots of the three choppers activated their electronic
anti-missile system and successfully evaded the missile.
</P>
<P>
The choppers and the passengers landed at Elephant Pass safely.
</P>
<P>
