<HEADLINE> China To Begin Official Securities Training Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- China will soon hold official
training programs for professionals in the securities business,
the China Securities reports today.
</P>
<P>
The China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC), in
collaboration with other government departments, is studying the
details of the training plan and a system of rating, the newspaper
said.
</P>
<P>
The qualifying of professionals in the securities business is a
common practice in many countries and regions, but in China it is
still at an initial stage, it said.
</P>
<P>
The existing training courses are unofficial, and the CSRC, the
industry watchdog, has not named any institution as an overseer of
training programs and qualifying exams for people in the
securities business.
</P>
<P>
Textbooks and testing plans are already being compiled, the
newspaper said.  
