<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Central Bank Tightens Cash Controls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China has
issued a circular calling for further controls on large
denomination bills.
</P>
<P>
The circular says that all financial organizations, including
banks and non-banking institutions like securities, trust and
investment, and finance companies should follow its rules on large
denomination bills.
</P>
<P>
The move is meant to curb economic crimes and protect financial
order and depositors' interests. It says that all banks should do
a thorough check on accounts by the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
It also said that finance, trust and investment, and leasing
companies can not handle individual savings deposits, and those
that are allowed to handle deposits must have strict controls on
the amount and term of deposit.
</P>
<P>
There must be strict controls on business accounts and on the
withdrawal of cash from accounts. Identity cards are necessary for
a withdrawal of more than 50,000 yuan, and for a withdrawal of
200,000 yuan or more, appointment by telephone a day ahead is
required. 
</P>
</TEXT>
