<HEADLINE> Malaysian Expedition Team to Visit Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kampala, October 7 (xinhua)-- A huge Malaysia expedition team
is to visit Uganda next month via southern Africa, the local
daily The Monitor said today.
</P>
<P>
The expedition is carrying with it hundreds of Malaysian
tourists and businessmen, Allen Peace Ampaire, sales and
marketing manager in the Nile Hotel International (NHI) in
Kampala was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Ampaire said the expedition code-named:"driving of love, hope
and friendship to Africa "is originating from Malaysia, through
the Pacific Ocean via the Cape of Good Hope in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
From Uganda, they will proceed to Cairo, Egypt, she added.
</P>
<P>
"President Nelson Mendela of South Africa is to receive the
expeditionists at the Cape. They will then drive by road through
Zimbabwe and Zambia where president Fredrick Chiluba is to
receive and flag them off to Tanzania," she said.
</P>
<P>
The team is expected to enter Uganda from Tanzania via Lake
Victoria at Port-Bell in southern Kampala on November 15, this
year.
</P>
<P>
The expedition is the first of its kind to Africa from outside
the continent and that 38 of the 85 hotel rooms have been booked
for the expeditionists, Ampaire disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan president Y. Museveni is expected to welcome the
expeditionists into the country, she said. 
