<HEADLINE> Indian Dairy Exports to Be More Competitive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Indian dairy exports will be
more competitive over the developed countries under the World
Trade Organization (WTO) regime, India's National Dairy
Development Board (NDDB) said here today.
</P>
<P>
Under the WTO regime, the developed countries will have to
reduce subsidies which will make their products costlier.
</P>
<P>
"While this presents a vast opportunity for us, our competitors
abroad would like to deny it to us," the NDDB said in its annual
report.
</P>
<P>
Among the measures being put into effect by the industrialized
countries are different forms of non-tariff trade barrier against
exports and the NDDB has asked the government to be aware of these
threats and prepare to meet them.  
</P>
