<HEADLINE> Toyota, of Japan, Opens Car Assembly Plant in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Toyota Motor Vietnam Co. Ltd.
(TMV) has opened a 90 million U.S. dollars car assembly plant
north of this Vietnamese capital.
</P>
<P>
Around 200 Corolla sedans, and Hiace vans are expected to roll
off each month from the plant's assembly line, which was
operational on Monday, said press reports here.
