<HEADLINE> Party School Professor on Joint Stock Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The report of the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) is a theoretical
breakthrough in the structure and form of ownership, a Chinese
professor said.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jue, a professor at the CPC Central Committee Party
School, says in an article in "China Securities News", that Jiang
Zemin's report is bound to have a powerful impact on China's
economic reforms and will avoid panic about privatization and
arouse the initiative of everyone in the current primary stage of
socialism.
</P>
<P>
The joint-stock system, which is a form of organizing capital
in the modern enterprise system, is more convenient for turning
large and medium-sized state-owned enterprises that have a direct
bearing on the nation's economy into market-oriented modern
companies, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
But, "we should not rush headlong into mass action in the joint
stock and stock co-operation. It is impossible to introduce the
two systems into all state-owned firms. These reforms should go
step by step under the leadership of the Party and government. In
this way the joint stock system reform can proceed in a healthy
way, he said. 
</P>
