<HEADLINE> Chinese Firm Compensated For Damaged Russian Fertilizer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Guangdong Agricultural
Materials Service Company has received 12 million yuan in
compensation for some damaged Russian fertilizer it received.
</P>
<P>
The Commodity Inspection Bureau in Guangzhou discovered that
13,000 tons of fertilizer out of a total of 36,000 tons that was
shipped from Russia had been seriously damaged by water when it
was being unloaded in Huangpu Port, in Guangzhou, in April.
</P>
<P>
Based on the bureau's first damage report, the provincial court
decided that the Russian ship could not leave the port unless a
160-million-US-dollar surety was paid.
</P>
<P>
A further investigation lasting two months set the net loss at
6,097 tons.  
