<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 09:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hijacking Attempt on Iranian Plane Foiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 7 (Xinhua) -- An armed hijacker of an Iranian
passenger plane Monday afternoon was subdued and arrested by
security guards on board, Iran's official news agency IRNA
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The domestic passenger plane of the Iran Air, flight No. 257,
was flying from capital Tehran to Bandar Abbas, an Iranian port
city in the south facing the Persian Gulf.
</P>
<P>
IRNA said that shortly after the plane took off, the hijacker,
about 30 years old, ordered the crew at gunpoint to change the
direction and fly to Iraq, Iran's long-time foe.
</P>
<P>
It said the man also mentioned Israel, a sworn enemy of Iran,
as an alternative destination.
</P>
<P>
It quoted passengers as saying that the hijacker then fired at
the cockpit and the flight crew to force the captain to change
route.
</P>
<P>
The security guards on board opened fire at the hijacker and
overpowered him, preventing any possible catastrophe. The hijacker
and the security guards were reportedly wounded.
</P>
<P>
There remain unclear the identity of the man and the objective
of his hijacking. IRNA gave no clue to whether he acted alone or
he had any accomplice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
