Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The spiritual leader of the Palestinian fundamentalist group
Hamas, Ahmed Yassin, Monday called for a continuation of armed
struggle against Israel when he left the Jordanian capital Amman for
Gaza. Meanwhile, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has
stressed that Israel is waging a total war without compromise
against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
-- French Minister of Finance and Economy Dominique Strauss-Kahn
announced on Monday that the government is selling the stocks of the
state monopoly France Telecom at 185-182 francs (about 30 US
dollars) per share. Meanwhile, institutional traders are already
selling the future shares of France Telcom at 200-210 francs (33.3
US dollars) per share. 
</P>
