<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Develops Advanced Petroleum Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- China has become a major figure
in the world's petroleum engineering and research, as well as in
production, according to Li Desheng, an academician at the Chinese
Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
Li, also chief geologist with the China National Petroleum
Corp.'s Research Institute of Petroleum Exploration and
Development, told Xinhua that China has a number of important
developments in continental petroleum geology, after decades of
research. This runs in conjunction with another theory on
hydrocarbon formation in marine geology.
</P>
<P>
The theory has enabled China to find 27 large oilfields with
reserves of more than 100 million tons each, like those at Daqing
in the Northeast and Renqiu in the North.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China has finally developed layer-by-layer oil
extraction technology, technology of stabilizing oil reserves by
injecting water, and using the polymer-drive extraction method.
</P>
<P>
Other major oilfields like Shengli, Liaohe, Zhongyuan, Huabei,
and Dagang in the Bohai Bay area have developed rolling
exploration technology, which has increased exploration, found
oil reserves of 7.28 billion tons and ensured annual crude output
of 61 million tons, making the bay the second largest oil and gas
production base after Daqing.
</P>
<P>
In the exploration of complex oil layers, China has come up
with thermodynamic technology to explore thick oil, mainly by the
use of steam and has developed an annual thick oil output of 12
million tons, the fourth largest in the world.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that by the turn of the century, China plans to
verify oil reserves totaling 2.5 billion to 3 billion tons and
pump 150 million tons of oil and 25 billion cu.m. of natural gas a
year.
</P>
<P>
To attain that goal, China is launching eight huge petroleum
science and technology projects, and 32 technological
developments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
