<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Cabinet Approves New Pay Scales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi cabinet approved
Monday new pay scales which will be implemented in phases, an
official press release said today.
</P>
<P>
The minimum salary is fixed at 1,600 taka (about 36.36 U.S.
dollars) including a lunch allowance of 100 taka (about 2.27
dollars), while the highest is 15,000 taka (about 340.90 dollars),
the release said.
</P>
<P>
The new scales will be implemented in a period of three years.
Sixty percent of the new salaries will be paid between July 1 this
year and June 1998, and the remaining 40 percent will be given
starting July 1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Until June 1999, festival allowance, bonus and other allowances
except lunch allowance will be paid on the basis of old salaries,
the release stated.
</P>
<P>
Allowances and bonus on the basis of new pay scales will be
given starting July 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
With the full implementation of the new pay scales, the lowest
salary will increase by 42 percent taking into account the
inflation rate, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet also decided to enhance the net pension by 10
percent in 1997-98 and 5 percent in 1998-99 considering the
problems of the pension holding government officers and employees,
the release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
