<HEADLINE> Philippines Putting Up Waste Facilities in Ports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Ports Authority
(PPA) has started putting up waste facilities nationwide to
improve ship and port waste management, the Philippine News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
PPA general manager Carlos Agustin said the move is an offshoot
of a memorandum of agreement signed on July 11 between the PPA and
the International Maritime Organization.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum demands the Philippines to take necessary steps
to improve its port waste system and includes plans to test the
waste facilities in the ports of Manila and Batangas which host
major port facilities.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the PPA also formed a committee to review the
proposals from the private sector to undertake a study on the
establishment of the facilities and the provision of related
services, Agustin said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the results of the study will be replicated in
other ports in the country.  
</P>
