<DOCNO> XIE19971007.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Petrochemical Company Improving Efficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Yangzi Petrochemical
Corp., a major state-owned enterprise in east China's Jiangsu
province, has spent more than 2.2 billion yuan upgrading
technology and equipment since it started full-scale production in
1990.
</P>
<P>
Most of the money has been spent on equipment to turn out
ethylene, PTA (purified terephthalic acid), and arene. Following
completion of the upgrading project at the end of this year, the
company will be able to increase its annual production capacity by
30 percent and reduce production costs.
</P>
<P>
Yangzi can now produce 400,000 tons of ethylene, 600,000 tons
of PTA, and 850,000 tons of arene a year, compared to the previous
300,000 tons of ethylene, 450,000 tons of PTA, and 640,000 tons of
arene.
</P>
<P>
It has scored an annual increase of over 20 percent in exports,
and in the first half of this year, exported 265,500 tons of
products worth 72.5 million US dollars, up 148 percent and 165
percent from the same period in 1996, respectively.
</P>
<P>
It has allocated two billion yuan to upgrade equipment to
manufacture ethylene, PTA, and arene, 540 million of that for
ethylene equipment, 700 million for PTA equipment, and 720 million
for arene equipment.
</P>
<P>
The improvement project began in 1994 and took three years to
complete. The company has tried hard to work in line with local
conditions and use as little investment as possible to improve
production instead of simply expanding production capacity.
</P>
<P>
The measures include inviting experts from the United States to
examine upgrading plans or inviting experts from equipment
manufacturers to provide advice.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the company has recovered 20 to 30 percent of its
investment on ethylene and PTA improvements, which were finished
in 1995 and 1996, respectively. All investment is expected to be
recovered within three to four years.
</P>
<P>
Arene production improvements will be finished by the end of
this year and investment is expected to be recovered in four years.
</P>
<P>
The value of the company's assets has doubled since 1990 to 19
billion yuan, and its asset-to-debt ratio dropped from 100 percent
to the present 44.46 percent.
</P>
<P>
The company made 590 million yuan in after-tax profits in the
first half of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
