<HEADLINE> Bulgaria To Sign National Minorities Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, October 6 (Xinhua) - Bulgarian President Peter Stoyanov
will sign the Framework Convention on the Protection of National
Minorities at the Council of Europe summit on October 9-11 in
Strasbourg, the Bulgarian Telegraph Agency (BTA) said today.
</P>
<P>
Before that, a draft of the translated declaration to the
convention will be read and reviewed in parliament by Foreign
Minister Mihailova along with the bill for its ratification.
</P>
<P>
The Council of Ministers decided to sign the convention on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The implementation of the convention will not change anything
inside Bulgaria, since the country is known for its tolerance to
ethnic groups whose rights are guaranteed by the constitution,"
Mihailova said. "But this would also give our country the moral
and legal justification to monitor the rights of Bulgarians
abroad." 
