<HEADLINE> Indonesian Haze Blankets Again Southern Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian haze has again
spread over parts of southern Thailand, according to reports
reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Favorable weather had last week cleared the smog which has been
caused by forest fires.
</P>
<P>
In the lower south, smog has been reported in Songkla, Satun,
Trang, Yala, Narathiwat and Phuket provinces.
</P>
<P>
In Songkla city, the visibility fell to 500 meters despite the
smell of smoke in the rain water. Hat Yai city was also blanketed
by smoky fog from early Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
Heavy smog was reported over the southernmost Betong District
of Yala Province.
</P>
<P>
The Betong municipality has distributed 4,000 cloth masks to
residents in addition to the 10,000 given out earlier. The
provincial public health office in Satun has ordered the
production of 30,000 cloth masks for distribution.  
</P>
