<HEADLINE> Earthquakes Hit Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measured 6.8 on the
Richter scale hit the southern Philippines Monday night,
Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology (PHIVOLCS) said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The PHIVOLCS said the quake was of tectonic origin. Its
epicenter was under the deep sea some kilometers northeast of
Siargao Island, Surigao del Norte province, the southern
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
An initial report by the PHIVOLCS said the quake was felt in
nearby areas, however, no casualties and property damage were
reported. Some Aftershocks are expected.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measured 5.1 on the Richter scale shook the
nearby area earlier the same day, the PHIVOLCS said, adding no one
was killed or wounded in the jolt. 
