<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Republic of Serbia's Agriculture Achieves Bumper Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Agriculture of The Republic
 of Serbia of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia achieved a bumper
harvest this year, a Serbian official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Jovan Babovic, minister of agriculture of the Republic of
Serbia of Yugoslavia, made the announcement when talking to Tanjug
news Agency.
</P>
<P>
Babovic said that Serbia's maize output this year amounted to
8.2 million tons, wheat 3.1 million tons, beet 2.3 million tons
and sunflower seeds 400,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural goods will not only be sufficient for the
domestic needs, but also be exported to other countries, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
