<HEADLINE> Thai Foreign Minister to Visit Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab
Chaiyasarn will pay a two-day official visit to Myanmar later this
month in a bid to strengthen bilateral relations while mending
ties between Myanmar and the European Union, according to
Permanent Secretary for Foreign Affairs Saroj Chavanaviraj.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between Thailand and Myanmar will top the agenda,
but relations between the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) and other regional grouping will be given high priority
during October 29-30 talks between Prachuab and his Myanmar
counterpart Ohn Gyaw, Saroj was quoted by local press as saying.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar and Laos were admitted into ASEAN in July. But, the
15-nation EU made clear its stance not to include Myanmar into a
1980 ASEAN-EU cooperation agreement which offers trade and
training benefits.
</P>
<P>
Thailand currently plays a role as a coordinator between ASEAN
and the EU.
</P>
<P>
Saroj said ASEAN foreign ministers agreed, during their
informal meeting on the sidelines of the United Nations' Assembly
on September 24 in New York, that no ASEAN members should be
excluded from that inter-regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"We(ASEAN) will uphold our principle that all ASEAN members are
subject to the (ASEAN-EU) agreement because it is a bloc-to-bloc
agreement," Saroj said.
</P>
<P>
Prachuab is expected to covey ASEAN's position when he meets
Manuel Marin, the European Commission's vice president who is in
charge of the EU's external economic cooperation, during his
official visit to Belgium on October 16.
</P>
<P>
Prachuab will also visit Spain for three days from October 13
to 15 before departing for Brussels.  
</P>
</TEXT>
