Petroleos de Venezuela (PDVSA) today announced a plan to invest 29
billion U.S. dollars before 2006.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, some 10.2 billion dollars will stem from foreign
banks, 8.5 billion from private partners, 8 billion from the
company's own stock revenues, while 3.1 billion dollars will come
from its capital, the company said.
