<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Boosting Tourism Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi
Province is making efforts to develop its key tourist areas,
hoping to show off its own unique style of tourism resources to
more overseas and domestic visitors.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent provincial plan, Shaanxi will emphasize
the development of the famous terra cotta figures of warriors and
horses dating back to the Qin Dynasty (221-207 B.C), the ancient
city of Xi'an, the picturesque Huashan Mountain, and the tomb of
Emperor Huang, known as the ancestor of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, a number of new tourist sites will also be
developed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, construction of basic tourist facilities will be
accelerated, with more domestic and international flight routes
added, work on high-grade highways with Xi'an as the center
speeded up, more tourist trains, and upgrading local
accommodation, catering, shopping, and entertainment facilities.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi is regarded as China's "natural museum of history," and
has been the capital city of 13 dynasties.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the province hosted nearly 210,000
overseas tourists in the first half of this year, a rise of 10.4
percent over the same period of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
