<HEADLINE> Tibetan Yaks Head for Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Tibetan yaks are providing a new
source of income for herdsmen in southwest China's Tibet
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The Guangxi Beihai Intl. Economic Development Ltd. Co. recently
signed a contract with four Tibetan companies to jointly develop
the yak industry.
</P>
<P>
In addition, new rapid growth, slaughtering and cold storage
technology have entered Tibet from other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Tibetans, who refer to yaks as "Treasures of the Plateau",
never fully realized the potential economic value of the animal.
</P>
<P>
"Large numbers of yaks formerly died during the harsh cold
winters in Tibet. Treasures turned to waste," according to
Professor Zhang, director of the Intl. Yak Information Center.
</P>
<P>
Tibetan yaks will enter both the domestic and international
markets. Tibet plans to establish an yak industry stock company in
the near future to develop the international market.
</P>
<P>
The "Mad Cow" epidemic in Britain, which alarmed European beef
lovers, has presented an excellent opportunity for Tibetan yaks to
enter the world market.
</P>
<P>
A symposium on the yak industry development will be held in
Tibet next Spring, according to the Tibetan Agriculture and Animal
Husbandry Department.  
</P>
</TEXT>
