<HEADLINE> First Ladies to Discuss Women's and Children's Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Twenty of the world's "first
ladies" will gather in Panama City this week to discuss women's
and children's rights, the First Lady of Panama, Dora Boyd de
Perez Balladares, said today.
</P>
<P>
The first ladies will attend a First Ladies' Conference of the
Americas on October 8-9 in the Atlalpa Conventions Center in
Panama City.
</P>
<P>
One of the top priorities of the meeting will be to awaken a
genuine concern for the plight of working children and to explore
solutions for their adequate physical and spiritual development
and improve their access to education and health services.
</P>
<P>
On the topic of women's issues, U.S. First Lady Hillary Clinton
is going to sign an accord granting 4.8 million dollars in aid to
support activities promoting legal rights for women.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also try to establish a financial fund in
order to involve women in industry and services, an initiative
expected to be supported by the Inter-American Development Bank.
