<HEADLINE> Second seed Bruguera Upset in First Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
VIENNA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Sergi Bruguera of
Spain was eliminated in the first round by Arnaud Clement of
France 6-2 7-6 (8-6) at the 800,000 U.S. dollars CA-Trophy men's
tennis tournament on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Swedes Jan Apell and Magnus Larsson entered the second round
with wins over Dutchman Jan Siemerink and Germany's Mark Kevin
Goellner respectively.
</P>
<P>
Appel, who is contesting only his second singles ATP
tournament this year because of a recurring shoulder injury, beat
last year's finalist Siemerink 6-2 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Larsson, the 1994 Grand Slam Cup winner, needed almost two
hours to beat Goellner 2-6 7-6 7-6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
