<HEADLINE> September Inflation Down in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Inflation in Italy fell to 1.4
percent in September from August's 1.5 percent, the National
Statistics Office, ISTAT, announced today.
</P>
<P>
It reported a monthly price rise of 0.2 percent and a
nine-month average inflation of 1.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The overall figure of 1.4 percent is in line with forecasts and
represents the lowest rate since February 1969. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
