<DOCNO> XIE19971007.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Improves Hi-Tech Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The hi-tech industry in the
Shenzhen Special Economic Zone, south China's Guangdong Province,
has witnessed annual growth of more than 70 percent since 1993.
</P>
<P>
The industry's output value of some 34.8 billion yuan in 1996
accounted for 28.7 percent of the local industrial total.
</P>
<P>
The city of Shenzhen has established leading industries related
to electronics information processing, telecommunications,
microelectronics and basic component sectors. The electronics and
information processing sectors generated 26 billion yuan, or
nearly 76 percent of the total output value for local hi-tech
sectors.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen will continue to focus on the computer and telecom
sectors, and will place greater emphasis on promoting biological
engineering and new materials.
</P>
<P>
the city plans to restructure its industrial layout by
establishing large hi-tech industrial development zones.
</P>
<P>
Local science and technology development organizations are
currently developing a new industrial park covering 11.2
sq.km. The new park is expected to become one of the city's major
hi-tech industrial bases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
