<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lausanne Loses World Cycling Track Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Swiss city Lausanne have lost the
right to host the year 2000 world cycling track championships, it
was announced in San Sebastian, Spain, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The International Cycling Union (UCI) said that no replacement
had been decided upon but the Colombian city of Cali are likely
to be one of the candidates, as they have already hosted a
previous championships.
</P>
<P>
Lausanne lost the right to host the championships because a
recent referendum said no to raising any more money for building
the stadium for the event.
</P>
<P>
The final decision as to which city wins the right to host the
championships will be taken in February 1998 -- Bordeaux are due
to have them next year and Berlin the year after. 
</P>
</TEXT>
