<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan Opens First Stomatological Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan
Province recently opened its first stomatological hospital.
</P>
<P>
The hospital, which was constructed at a cost of more than 20
million yuan, is equipped with state-of-the-art medical equipment
for treating stomatological diseases and performing plastic
surgery. It is located in Kunming, capital of the province.
</P>
<P>
Kunming was formerly home to over 100 stomatological clinics.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that over half of China's 1.2 billion people
suffer from some type of dental disease, while only however, two
of every 10,000 medical professionals are dentists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971007.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Reservoir to Become China's Largest Fishpond </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing Municipality will
turn the Three Gorges reservoir area into China's largest fishpond
using box-like nets.
</P>
<P>
The city, which faces the Yangtze River but has a limited
supply of fish, initiated a technique in 1989 to raise fish in
large nets, which ensured 200-300 kg of fish yield per square
meter.
</P>
<P>
The damming of the river for the Three Gorges reservoir offers
Chongqing good opportunities to breed fish on a larger and more
intensive scale, as the project will help form a water area of
more than 1,000 sq. km.
</P>
<P>
Some 30 percent of the water area can be used for fish raising,
said Sun Pengshou, director of the city's Aquatics Science and
Technology Spreading Station, adding that the new method will take
the place of pond and paddy field fish-raising in the city.
</P>
<P>
The heavy water flow, high flow speed and high silt content
have hindered the development of the new method in the past eight
years.
</P>
<P>
However, the damming project has unveiled bright prospects, as
it will make it possible to have a stable water flow and also
regular runoff, which are especially helpful in fish raising.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
