<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Opens New Drug Rehabilitation Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fuzhou, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A new drug rehabilitation center
in Fuzhou, capital of east China's Fujian Province. is currently
providing compulsory rehabilitation and education to 74 drug
addicts.
</P>
<P>
Fuzhou has introduced strong measures to crack down on
drug-related crime and is extending greater efforts to reinforce
drug rehabilitation drive. The city allocated special funds of
some 2.8 million yuan (343,400 US dollars) in 1997 to establish
the drug rehabilitation center, which covers 2,000 sq.m. and has
300 beds. The center restricts the movement of addicts as part of
the rehabilitation program.
</P>
<P>
The Fuzhou city government considers drug control as an
important aspect in achieving security and social stability. The
government fully supports all public security departments and has
achieved significant progress in eliminating drug cultivation,
consumption and trafficking. Statistics show that 705 narcotics
cases have been prosecuted, with the arrest of 1,494 producers of
illegal drugs, traffickers and addicts leading to the confiscation
of 207.3 kilogram heroin, 8.4 kilogram opium and 415.8 kilogram
ice.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
