<HEADLINE> Canada to Promote Exports with New Initiatives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Canada announced today a series
of new measures to enhance the government's trade promotion
services and help Canadian firms increase their exports.
</P>
<P>
The new initiatives enhance existing services in Canada's trade
promotion network, which was designated "Team Canada Inc." today
by International Trade Minister Sergio Marchi.
</P>
<P>
Marchi outlined five new initiatives under Team Canada Inc:
</P>
<P>
-- the establishment of a Team Canada Inc Advisory Board;
</P>
<P>
-- a 30-percent increase in the number of trade commissioners
assigned outside Canada;
</P>
<P>
-- a new unit at the Department of Foreign Affairs and
International Trade to focus on the export needs of small and
medium-sized enterprises;
</P>
<P>
-- an enhanced 24-hour trade access service that connects to
trade centres across the country;
</P>
<P>
-- and an integrated, results-oriented business plan for trade
and investment promotion.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that all levels of governments and private
sector must work together as partners to encourage and assist
Canadian companies in selling their products and services around
the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
