<HEADLINE> Heritage Loss Results From Lacking Control: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Minister of
Information and Culture Woldemichael Chemu said today the ever
increasing loss of heritages can be attributed to nothing but
lack of effective control and protection.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a training course prepared for regional heritage
experts, the minister said the existing condition in the loss of
heritages is very shameful for the generation and could gradually
dwindle the country's heritages.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that every one should stand against such threat.
</P>
<P>
In order to preserve heritages in a proper manner, it is
necessary to identify them in their type and their present
condition and have a tight protection, Chemu said.
</P>
<P>
The minister added that it is decisive to build the capacity
of regions to accomplish the task.
</P>
<P>
He also said the training program is prepared to develop the
capacity of trained manpower in the field. 
