<HEADLINE> Jordan Releases Alleged Israeli Agents Attacking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Jordan released this afternoon
two alleged Israeli agents and all the others detained for
attempting to kill a Hamas leader in Jordan last month, according
to senior Jordanian government officials.
</P>
<P>
The release was the result of "a good bargain" between Jordan
and Israel in exchange for the release of Hamas founder Sheikh
Ahmed Yassin by Israel on October 1, the officials who declined to
be named said.
</P>
<P>
Yasser, jailed by Israel in 1989 and expected to serve a life
sentence for ordering attacks by Hamas guerrillas against Israeli
targets, arrived in the Gaza Strip this afternoon from Amman. He
was released on demand by Jordan's King Hussein.
</P>
<P>
As part of the bargain, Israel also agreed to save the life of
Khaled Mashal, head of Hamas political bureau, by giving the
medicine that helped him defeat vomit and coma caused by the
attack against him by the two alleged special agents from Israeli
secret service Mossad.
</P>
<P>
On September 25, the two men attempted to kill Mashal in front
of his office, but were arrested following the failed attempt.
</P>
<P>
Hamas was established in 1987 to fight against Israel`s
occupation of Palestine. Most Hamas political bureau members live
in Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Jordan signed a peace treaty with Israel in 1994 and is now
one of the two Arab countries that conceived peace with the
Jewish state. 
