<DOCNO> XIE19971007.0273 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Third Euro-Mediterranean Industrial Summit Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The third Euro-Mediterranean
industrial summit opened here today with the aim of discussing
progress towards a Euro-Mediterranean partnership and
recommendations for a Euro-Mediterranean zone.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of industry federations from 31 countries of
Europe and the Mediterranean basin are participating in the
two-day summit which was organized by the Federation of Greek
Industries, the Development Ministry, the European Commission and
the Union of Industrial and Employers' Confederations of Europe.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the conference, Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis
said that the creation of a uniform Euro-Mediterranean region was
a challenge for the entire area and for each country.
</P>
<P>
The policy of the Euro-Mediterranean partnership, through the
creation of a comprehensive forum of association between the
European Union (EU) and its Mediterranean partners, would enable
the Mediterranean basin to become an area of strengthened
political dialogue, transactions and cooperation in ways that
would guarantee peace, stability and prosperity, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
